Kimberley is gearing up to welcome thousands of ANC members for this year's January 8 speech. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the ANC's annual January 8 Statement in Kimberley on Saturday. The statement which sets the tone for the year coincides with the ruling party's 108th anniversary. WATCH: Ramaphosa speaks as ANC turns 108 This year's event comes at a time of massive economic challenges in the country largely blamed on the ongoing electricity crisis. The premature reintroduction of load-shedding led to the sudden resignation of Eskom's Chair, Jabu Mabuza.